Karma with Jasmine:
-------------------

    - We have Two Types Of Testings.

        1. Manual Testing
            [Now a days no body using Manual Testing]

        2. Automation Testing.
            [Now a days all most all the projects using Automation Testing]

    - Karma is the Testing Framework used to perform Automation Testing on UI Applications

        Ex.
            AngularJS
            Angular4
            reactJS
            NodeJS
                --
                --
                --

     - Automation Testing categorized into 3 types.

     1. unit testing

     2. integration testing

     3. end to end testing.



1. unit testing
---------------
    - checking the perticular functionality with dummy scenarios called as unit testing.


2. integration testing
----------------------
    - checking the perticular functionality with real scenarios called as integration testing.

3. end to end testing:
---------------------
    - checking whole application with different end points (api points, physical connections) called as
      end to end testing.


Installation Of Karma:
----------------------
>npm install -g karma


Testing Controller:
------------------

var app = angular.module("app",[]);

app.controller("ctrl",ctrl);
function ctrl($scope){
    $scope.var_one = "AngularJS";
}


app.controller("test",test){
    $scope.my_fun = function(){
        return "Welcome";
    };
};


//write the test spec.

karma.conf.js
-------------

//define the test suite.
describe("testing the controller",function(){
    var $controller;
    //accessing the app module to testing environment.
    module("app");
    //accessing the controller to test suite.
    inject("accessing the controllers",function(_$controller_){
        $controller = _$controller_;
    });
)};


it("unit test case one",function(){
    var result = $controller.get("ctrl",{$scope:$scope});
    expect(result).equalTo("AngularJS")
        "/******Unit Test Success*****/"

    "/************Unit Test case Fail*****/"


});


it("testing the test controller",function(){
    var result = $controller.get("test",{$scope:$scope});
    var value= result.my_fun();

    expect(value).equalTo("Welcome")
        /****Test Case Success !!!******/

    /***Test Case Failed****/

});



>karma start





Testing the Service:
--------------------

var app = angular.module("app",[]);
app.factory("my_service",my_service);
function my_service(){
    return ["AngularJS","Angular4","NodeJS","MongoDB"];
}


describe("testing service",function(){
    var testServices;

    module("app");
    inject("testing service...",function(injector){
        testServices=injector;
    });

});

it("hello test msg",function(){
    var array = testServices.get("my_service");

    array.contains("AngularJS");
    array.contains("Angular4");
    array.contains("NodeJS");
    array.contains("MongoDB");
    array.equalsTo(4);
        /****Test Case Success !****/
    /****Test Case Fail !****/

});
































